&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ready to do the most impactful work of your career? At&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.coinbase.com/?utm_campaign=mt_o_m_w_m_m__coi_0_jd-onchain&amp;amp;utm_source=coinbase&quot;&gt;Coinbase&lt;/a&gt;, we are uncompromising on our mission to increase economic freedom. The bar is high, the environment is intense, and we like it that way. This isn&#39;t a place for complacency, it’s a place to be pushed past your perceived limits. If you&#39;re ready to build the future of finance alongside people who refuse to settle for &quot;good enough,&quot; you belong here. Coinbase is a remote-first, but not remote-only company. Expect to get together quarterly for intense in-person working sessions called “surges.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.coinbase.com/careers&quot;&gt;learn more about working at Coinbase&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;mb-2 whitespace-pre-wrap&quot;&gt;As an Accounting Manager, Prime Financing, you&#39;ll join the Accounting team within Finance and own the end-to-end accounting function for Coinbase&#39;s prime financing and brokerage business. Reporting to the Assistant Controller, Prime Brokerage and Digital Assets, you&#39;ll build processes and controls from the ground up, lead a team through monthly close and quarterly/annual reporting, and partner cross-functionally to ensure accurate financial reporting as this business scales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;mb-2 whitespace-pre-wrap&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the review and approval of monthly financing accounting entries, reconciliations, and supporting documentation to ensure accuracy and completeness through each close cycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable, automated financial processes and controls for the prime financing function, including drafting standard operating procedures that reduce manual effort and support SOX compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead your team through the monthly financial close, quarterly reporting, and annual audit processes, ensuring deadlines are met and deliverables are audit-ready.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams to provide accounting insights on SEC regulations and lending practices, translating regulatory developments into actionable accounting guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the design and implementation of new controls and processes for platform and brokerage accounting activities, identifying gaps and recommending improvements that keep pace with business growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;mb-2 whitespace-pre-wrap&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills and Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPA designation with 9+ years of progressive accounting experience, including a mix of Big 4 public accounting and industry roles in fintech or financial services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct experience with financing, lending, or prime brokerage accounting at a publicly traded company, including familiarity with SEC reporting requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of building accounting processes and internal controls from the ground up, including designing SOPs and implementing automation that reduced close timelines or error rates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing or leading a team through monthly close cycles and quarterly/annual reporting, with demonstrated ability to meet tight regulatory deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working proficiency in NetSuite, FloQast, and Google Suite, with the ability to leverage these tools to streamline close and reporting workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilizes generative AI responsibly, maintaining human oversight to deliver business-ready outputs and drive measurable improvements in workflow efficiency, cost, and quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job #: P75544&lt;/p&gt;
